        { "mark": "M1", "desc": "Denominator factorised: $(x + 3)(x - 2)$" },
        { "mark": "A1", "desc": "$\\dfrac{x - 3}{x - 2}$ cao" }
      ],
      "workingSteps": [
        "Numerator: $x^2 - 9 = (x - 3)(x + 3)$",
        "Denominator: $x^2 + x - 6$; need product $-6$, sum $+1$: $+3$ and $-2$",
        "$x^2 + x - 6 = (x + 3)(x - 2)$",
        "$\\dfrac{(x-3)(x+3)}{(x+3)(x-2)} = \\dfrac{x-3}{x-2}$ (cancelling $x+3$)",
        "Check $x=5$: $\\frac{25-9}{25+5-6}=\\frac{16}{24}=\\frac{2}{3}$; answer: $\\frac{5-3}{5-2}=\\frac{2}{3}$ ✓"
      ],
      "explanation": "Factorise numerator and denominator separately, then cancel the common factor."
